14 department, including, but not limited to, mowing, herbicide
15 application, grassing, replanting with native species whenever
16 practicable, limb management, tree removal and debris removal; (3)
17 beautification, enhancements and the effect on scenic roads designated
18 pursuant to section 13b-31c; (4) visibility enhancement; and (5) the
19 environmental impact of such work, including (A) preventing invasive
20 tree, brush or plant species' growth and impact, (B) storm water run-off,
21 (C) erosion, (D) replanting of vegetation species to expand and improve
22 pollinator habitats, as described in section 22-90b, and (E) reduced
23 mowing. Such guidelines shall apply to construction projects financed,
24 in whole or in part, with federal funds to the extent such guidelines do
25 not conflict with federal laws and regulations.
26 (c) Such guidelines shall not apply to the removal of any trees or
27 vegetation necessary to maintain public safety or that is performed
28 because of a weather-related civil preparedness emergency declared
29 pursuant to section 28-9.
30 (d) [On or before January 1, 2024] Not later than February 1, 2027, the
31 Commissioner of Transportation shall consider the results of the study
32 and recommendations conducted pursuant to section 63 of public act
33 24-151, as amended by this act, by the Department of Natural Resources
34 and the Environment at The University of Connecticut concerning the
35 carbon sequestration by trees and other vegetation along highways and
36 other areas in the state , and determine the need, if any, for revisions to
37 the guidelines adopted pursuant to subsection (a) of this section. If the
38 commissioner determines a revision to such guidelines is not warranted,
39 the commissioner shall submit a report, in accordance with the
40 provisions of section 11-4a, to the joint standing committees of the
41 General Assembly having cognizance of matters relating to
42 transportation and the environment explaining the reasons for such
43 determination. If the commissioner revises such guidelines in response
44 to the results of such study, the commissioner shall submit such revised
45 guidelines to [the] such joint standing committees, [of the General
46 Assembly having cognizance of matters relating to transportation and
47 the environment,] in accordance with the provisions of section 11-4a.
